import React, { useState } from 'react'; function Signup() { const [user, setUser] = useState({ username: '', email: '', password: '', city: '', stateCode: '', countryCode: '' }); const onChange = (event) => { setUser({ ...user, [event.target.name]: event.target.value }); }; const signup = () => { fetch('http://localhost:8080/signup', { method: 'POST', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }, body: JSON.stringify(user) }) .then((res) => { console.log('Signup successful!', res); }) .catch((err) => { console.error('Signup failed:', err); }); }; return (

); } export default Signup;
